{
  "stem": "19550.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And that was one of the reasons why he halted the deportation at a certain point.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It was after-- that resumed, of course, when he fell in October 15th, I believe, of 1944.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Even though that he, he was a, a dyed-in-the-wool anti-Semite-- but he was a gentlemanly anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And he would not have thought of burning Jews-- or certainly had some concern for the image of Hungary in, in the world.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And so he was ready to dispense with these Northeastern Jews who were really basically the Galician Jews.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And they were not really Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and, of course, the population was aware of this attitude.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And in some ways, it was a kind of symbiotic relationship.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Because on the one hand, that was the demand of the population to which the authorities responded.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And on the other hand, the authorities have encouraged that attitude.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there was, as I said, this, this wall that existed between the, the various elements of the non-Jewish community and, and the various elements of the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It depended on, on-- its, its nature or its character depended on the nature of the elements of the community.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "If you were a Hasidic Jew, obviously, you were a stranger.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if you were a plain peasant in Hungary, you may have even had warm feelings towards the Jews.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you wouldn't want to get involved with them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You wouldn't want to become, you know, not only not part of their family, but you wouldn't want to be involved in their existence and in their life, and vice versa, obviously.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, to, to the Jews, in a way, the non-Jews were primitive, uncouth.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
